definitions.definition: A partly-recognized country on the Balkan Peninsula in Southeast Europe . Official name: Republic of Kosovo . Capital and largest city: Pristina . Considered by the Republic of Serbia to be one of its two autonomous provinces.
One of five administrative districts of the above region as viewed by the Serbian government.
